description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

2. Compile using the following command:

ajc subpackage\Test.java

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory. This means running the java command results in the exception "java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test".

Running the following command fixes the problem: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java.
